# Root system / acceptance test skeleton
#
# One file per root scope. Rendered to: <paths.tests>/system/<scope>_system_test.<ext>
# Tag or annotate as system tests — these do not run in the unit or integration suite.
#
# Placeholders:
#   <<SCOPE>>         scope path slug (typically "root" or the product name)
#   <<CASE_ID>>       TestSpec case id (e.g., TC-001 at root)
#   <<VERIFIES_IDS>>  REQ-NNN and PB-outcome-NNN IDs from case verifies: field
#   <<TEST_NAME>>     derived from case title (the user journey)
#   <<ENVIRONMENT>>   named environment tier from preconditions: (e.g., "staging-blue")
#   <<PERSONA>>       named persona from preconditions:
#   <<TENANT>>        named test tenant from preconditions:
#   <<FEATURE_FLAGS>> feature flag state from preconditions:
#   <<STEPS>>         user-journey driver calls (one per step: item)
#   <<ASSERT>>        business / user-visible assertions (one per expected: item)
#
# Key rule: assertions use user-visible and business-visible state only.
# No internal class names, no HTTP status codes, no internal API terms.
# See references/layer-rendering.md §Root.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

